This article is a transcript of a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Josh Earnest. The briefing covers a variety of topics, including the recent reports of sexual abuse by Afghan soldiers, the upcoming visit of Pope Francis, the situation in Yemen, and the fight against ISIS. Earnest also addresses questions about General John Allen potentially stepping down as the envoy in the US coalition to fight ISIS, and the potential government shutdown. He emphasizes the importance of bipartisan cooperation in Congress and the need for Republicans to work with Democrats to prevent a government shutdown.